{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AWXbP5hoxFMhe1PpyRwYsE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: query-layer-discipline\n     3→description: Scaffold queryset/manager/selector layers and wire view reads through selector entrypoints with jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Query Layer Discipline (Jig)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill to standardize read paths through QuerySet + selector layers.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `model_name`\n    13→- `queryset_name`\n    14→- `manager_name`\n    15→- `selector_name`\n    16→- `selector_file`\n    17→- `view_name`\n    18→\n    19→## Usage\n    20→\n    21→```bash\n    22→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\n    23→  \"model_name\": \"Entity\",\n    24→  \"queryset_name\": \"EntityQuerySet\",\n    25→  \"manager_name\": \"EntityManager\",\n    26→  \"selector_name\": \"select_active_entities\",\n    27→  \"selector_file\": \"selectors.py\",\n    28→  \"view_name\": \"entity_list\"\n    29→}'\n    30→```\n    31→\n    32→If jig fails, use rendered snippets from stderr as manual patch guidance.\n    33→\n    34→Notes:\n    35→- The recipe anchors to the first class in `models_file` and first function in `views_file`.\n    36→- Use focused files when running this skill so anchors are deterministic.\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5a815395-dc98-4a96-8361-9b677c00137e","uuid":"2543daae-1d37-4e94-ae5c-957b3f516853"}
